3. Check uninstall:

marcilr@boothite:~$ dpkg -l | grep virtualbox
rc  virtualbox-ose      3.2.10-dfsg-1   x86 virtualization solution - base binaries
rc  virtualbox-ose-qt   3.2.10-dfsg-1   x86 virtualization solution - Qt based user 
                                        interface

Run /root/bin/purge to clear out rc turds:
boothite:~# purge

Looks good:
marcilr@boothite:~$ dpkg -l | grep virtualbox
marcilr@boothite:~$


4. Install virtualbox 4.0.8:
boothite:~# dpkg --install virtualbox-4.0_4.0.8-71778-Debian-squeeze_amd64.deb

marcilr@boothite:~$ dpkg -l | grep virtualbox
ii  virtualbox-4.0                        4.0.8-71778~Debian~squeeze        Oracle VM VirtualBox

Installed VirtualBox v4.0.8 r71778

In gnome now have:
  Applications > System Tools > Oracle VM VirtualBox




